# PlanMyJob — Git PR & go cleanup

Follow the global **Git PR Cleanup Workflow** (`go cleanup` / `go cleaning`).

## This repo

- **Default branch** : `master`
- **Protection** : merge via PR only — check CI **`Lint, test & build`** required
- **PR link** : `https://github.com/OliviaG-dev/PlanMyJob/compare/master...<branch>`
- **After merge** : CI puis CD Vercel production (preview déjà déployée sur la PR)

## When user asks add / commit / push

1. Commit on a feature branch (not `master` unless explicitly requested and allowed).
2. Push and share the PR link.
3. Ask to **merge on GitHub**.
4. Ask to send **`go cleanup`** after merge, then run the global cleanup steps.

See also `docs/branch-protection.md`.
